Life Expectancy Prediction using ANN
This project demonstrates Life Expectancy prediction using Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs). The goal is to build a regression model that predicts the life expectancy of countries based on various health and demographic factors.

📌 Project Overview
Objective: Predict life expectancy using historical health, economic, and demographic data.

Approach: Perform data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and train an ANN regression model.

Tools & Libraries: Python, TensorFlow/Keras, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn.

📂 Repository Structure
bash
Copy
Edit
Life_Expectancy_Regression_Using_ANN/
│
├── Life_expectancy_Regression_Using_ANN.ipynb   # Main Jupyter Notebook
├── README.md                                    # Project Documentation
└── requirements.txt                             # Required Python packages
🔹 Key Steps in the Notebook
Data Loading & Cleaning

Import dataset

Handle missing values and data inconsistencies

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Visualize distributions, correlations, and trends

Identify outliers and skewed features

Feature Engineering & Preprocessing

Normalize/standardize features

Handle categorical variables (if any)

Train-test split

Building the ANN Model

Define an Artificial Neural Network with multiple hidden layers

Use activation functions like ReLU and output layer with linear activation

Compile the model with optimizer (Adam) and loss (MSE)

Model Training & Evaluation

Train using early stopping and dropout for regularization

Evaluate model performance using RMSE, MAE, and R² score

Visualization

Plot training vs validation loss

Predicted vs Actual life expectancy

